Weather Web App
Description
The Weather Web App is a simple web application built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript that allows users to search for the weather of different cities around the world. It provides real-time weather information, including temperature, weather conditions, and forecasts for a given location.

Features
City Search: Users can search for the weather of any city by entering the city name in the search bar.

Weather Information: The app displays current weather information, including temperature (in Celsius or Fahrenheit), weather conditions (e.g., sunny, cloudy, rainy), and a brief description.

Forecast: Users can also view a 3-day weather forecast for the selected city, including high and low temperatures.

Technologies Used
HTML: Used for creating the structure and content of the web page.

CSS: Used for styling the user interface and making it visually appealing.

JavaScript: Used for fetching weather data from an API, handling user interactions, and updating the UI dynamically.
